Olaleye Aluko, Abuja A  Nigerian Army corporal  fighting insurgency in the North-East  has shot dead  four  of his colleagues, injuring two others. The acting Director, Army Public Relations, Col Sagir Musa,  said  in a statement the unnamed corporal also shot himself during the shock incident which took place   at the Army Super Camp 15, located in  Malam Fatori, Borno State, in the early hours of Wednesday. According to him, the two injured soldiers  were rushed to a military hospital in Maiduguri. Musa said the army hierarchy  had ordered  investigation into the case. He said, “A corporal of the army serving at the Theatre Command, Operation Lafiya Dole, Army Super Camp 15, located at Malam Fatori went berserk in the early hours of Wednesday and opened fire, killing four of his colleagues before shooting himself. “Two of his colleagues were also injured during the incident and are in stable conditions in our hospital in Maiduguri. Efforts are on to contact the families of our gallant colleagues who paid the supreme price in the line of duty.” Copyright PUNCH.
